<item>
            <title>[LU-15105] sanity test_418: df and lfs df inodes output mismatch</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15105</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/495b6fac-69f3-4368-b3c6-ecafcbe601b6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/495b6fac-69f3-4368-b3c6-ecafcbe601b6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_418 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;df and lfs df inodes output mismatch:  df -i: 10.2.8.122@tcp:/lustre 3355456 19453 3336003 1% /mnt/lustre,  lfs df -i: filesystem_summary: 3355456 19254 3336202 1% /mnt/lustre
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is separate from the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13997&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_418: df and lfs df blocks output mismatch&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13997&quot;&gt;LU-13997&lt;/a&gt; &lt;b&gt;blocks&lt;/b&gt; mismatch, but is instead an &lt;b&gt;inodes&lt;/b&gt; mismatch and very likely has a different root cause.  The sanity test_418 fails with an inode mismatch about 1/10 as often as the block mismatch, so was incorrectly diagnosed as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13997&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_418: df and lfs df blocks output mismatch&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13997&quot;&gt;LU-13997&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;





&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity test_418 - df and lfs df inodes output mismatch:  df -i: 10.2.8.122@tcp:/lustre 3355456 19453 3336003 1% /mnt/lustre,  lfs df -i: filesystem_summary: 3355456 19254 3336202 1% /mnt/lustre&lt;/p&gt;</description>
